HEADWORD: Turnbulls blue
<hw>Turn"bull's blue`</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧rn"b⟦usdot⟧lz bl⟦umac⟧`)</pr>.
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The double cyanide of ferrous and ferric iron, a
dark blue amorphous substance having a coppery luster, used in dyeing,
calico printing, etc. Cf. <cref>Prussian blue</cref>, under
<er>Prussian</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turncoat</ent>⟦br⟧
